history.content:
Waitlists have not been processing automatically since Friday, February 3 (end of third week of classes).

After that point, any student enrolled in any cs class has to be processed manually by department staff. That is still occurring for most classes including CS188 (there is another piazza post that makes that clear class by class).  

That will happen until campus deadline of end of 5th week (Friday, February 17).  After that department staff is unable to process waitlists.  Late adds after that require approval at the level of the Dean -- if you look under forms on your college's advising website you can find them -- and that won't happen just because you didn't get in earlier but will require an extraordinary reason.

What is the deadline of automatic enrollment processing for the 188 waitlist? I am currently number 15 in the waitlist, but I do not know what to expect. Can someone explain what would happen if the deadline passes for enrollment and are the professors allowed to let some students in from the waitlist if they want to?
history.subject: CS 188 waitlist
